Maybe this is useful for you :)

I added some less mixins to add icons to any element/selector

usage:

```LESS
.my-button {
    .icon-full(@icon-download);
    /* custom styles */
}
.my-other-button {
    .icon-full(@icon-barcode, 1.5, #f00);
    /* other styles */
}
.another-button {
    .icon-lite(@icon-qrcode, 1, #0f0);
    /* other styles */
}
```

compiles to

```CSS
.my-button:before {
  font-family:FontAwesome;
  font-weight:normal;
  font-style:normal;
  display:inline-block;
  line-height:1em;
  vertical-align:middle;
  text-align:center;
  width:1em;
  margin-right:0.2em;
  content:"\f01a";
  font-size:1em;
  line-height:1em;
  color:inherit;
}
.my-other-button:before {
  font-family:FontAwesome;
  font-weight:normal;
  font-style:normal;
  display:inline-block;
  line-height:1em;
  vertical-align:middle;
  text-align:center;
  width:1em;
  margin-right:0.2em;
  content:"\f02a";
  font-size:1.5em;
  line-height:0.666666666667em;
  color:#ff0000;
}
.another-button:before {
  margin-right:0.2em;
  content:"\f029";
  font-size:1em;
  line-height:1em;
  color:#00ff00;
}
```

HTML example:

```HTML
<a href="#" class="my-button">click me</a>
<a href="#" class="my-other-button">click me too</a>
<a href="#" class="another-button icon">or click me</a>
```
